# ai-paas environment variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values:
#   cp .env.example .env
#
# .env is git-ignored. Never commit .env with real secrets.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Web UI credentials
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
UI_USERNAME=admin
UI_PASSWORD=your-password

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional — HuggingFace token for gated models
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# HF_TOKEN=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Model storage — absolute paths on HOST
# MODELS_PATH: root directory for ALL models (vLLM + ComfyUI).
#   Default (if not set): ./models  (relative to repo root)
#   Override example: /mnt/hdd/ai-models
# COMFYUI_MODELS_HDD: extra optional HDD mount for large ComfyUI models.
#   Only needed if you want a secondary mount inside the container.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# MODELS_PATH=/home/youruser/ai-paas/models
# COMFYUI_MODELS_HDD=/mnt/hdd/comfyui-models

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Optional — yt-dlp cookie file for YouTube authentication
# Enables access to age-restricted, member-only, and private videos.
# The cookie-manager container auto-generates this file.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# YTDLP_COOKIES_PATH=/cookies/cookies.txt

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Media storage — NFS or local path on HOST for downloaded videos/subtitles.
# The /download page saves files here. Subdirectories are auto-discovered
# and shown as a dropdown in the WebUI.
# Example: /mnt/truenas/media
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# MEDIA_ROOT=/mnt/truenas/media
